node.text: PLEASE READ!! As some of you might know I was in the water when my best friend got her arm bite off by a tiger shark. For many years after (especially after having a kid) I would think about the attack and even dream about sharks trying to get me. I developed a fear of sharks and every time I surfed I would get this crazy hit of  anxiety  that I would have to talk myself out of. Since surfing and being in the water is my life Iv been trying to work on this and educate myself on sharks and there behavior. Then almost 17 years later  a tiger shark named Riley came and said hello while diving with @oceanramsey and @juansharks I never thought I would be swimming with something I feared for so long. Riley did about 4 passes by us and I was able to dive down and make eye contact, it was beautiful and I’ll alway remember it. I had tears of joy instead of this fear I thought I would of have. It was peaceful and it was like he was telling me something..... they are not the thing we need to fear. I know this can be hard to wrap your head around but shark attacks are very rare and they don’t see us as food. All I know is we need to save these amazing creatures. We need them more then they need us. If you guys want more info please go to @oceanramsey and @juansharks they are experts in all things sharks. #helpsavesharks #savethesharks NO #sharkfinsoup #learnaboutsharks 🎥 @jaketaiwan4

node.text: Thank you to everyone that wrote me about my recent YouTube video. I talked about a few things I went through with a sponsor I had during the time I became a mom. I got told I couldn’t be shot next to the 18 year old models anymore and that I looked tired and was breastfeeding...... long story short it has been on my mind so much this pregnancy because I didn’t realize until recently how much those words have effected me. For so many years women have been told just like I have that they need to look a certain way to be called beautiful. I do believe that times are changing and shedding light on issues like this is very important. I think no matter what stage of life your going through it should be celebrated and not made to feel like we should all look like 18 year old models. You are beautiful and unique just the way you are💙 video is linked in my bio.

I have to keep reminding myself that I won’t be pregnant for ever even though right now it feels that way.

Women’s bodies are truly incredible and should be celebrated at every stage, size, age etc.
